It was at this time the consul invented an immense machine to counteract the mechanism of Archimedes, and in which he fully confided for success. He chained to- gether sideways, in the strongest manner he was able, eight of his stoutest gallies of different lengths, here- by incorporating them into one moveable bridge, which was to be rowed by the oars of the extreme gallies alone. On this powerful basis he raised a structure of a height superior to that of the towers of the Syracusan ramparts, at the summit of which was a platform, capable of containing a vast body of sol- dier-s, and protected by parapets both in front and on either side.
